<subSubSection lastPageId="191" lastPageNumber="794" pageId="190" pageNumber="793" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="190.[1373,2577,3207,3476]" pageId="190" pageNumber="793">
Taxonomy, identification, and distribution confused. According to the 2014 findings ofJ. Bryja and colleagues, Tanzanian records should be attributed to a distinct species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1800" box="[1375,1529,3325,3359]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="190" pageNumber="793" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gerbillus">M. gerbillus</taxonomicName>
, which is currently included within the synonymy of the present species. Also, in 2005, G. G.Musser and M. D. Carleton concluded that many of the Ethiopian records normally attributed to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[1821,1964,3403,3437]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Mus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="190" pageNumber="793" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tenellus">M. tenellus</taxonomicName>
(and possibly other mapped records from Somalia and Sudan) are apparently misidentified 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Smith" authorityYear="1834" box="[2076,2261,3447,3476]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Mus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="190" pageNumber="793" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minutoides">M. minutoides</taxonomicName>
. For the present work,
</paragraph>
<subSubSection box="[97,940,3291,3320]" pageId="190" pageNumber="793" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="190.[97,1305,2554,3479]" box="[97,940,3291,3320]" pageId="190" pageNumber="793">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[97,332,3291,3320]" pageId="190" pageNumber="793">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
